    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-07-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-07-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="105"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 180/48 A.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Dawson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 23, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President Montt, of Chile, will arrive at Panama on the 25th or 26th instant on
                    board the Chilean warship <hi rend="italic">Esmeralda</hi>, on his way to <pb
                        facs="0243" n="131" xml:id="pg_131"/> Europe for the benefit of his health.
                    You will cooperate with the authorities of the Canal Zone and exert every effort
                    to make his stay in Panama as agreeable as possible and to facilitate the ease
                    of his transit across the territory of Panama.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
